==English==

===Etymology===
From {{m|en|Christian}} + {{m|en|name}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A [[first name]] formally given to a child at a Christian baptism.
# {{lb|en|by extension}} Any [[forename]].
# {{lb|en|Singapore}} An English [[given name]], particularly for ethnic [[Chinese]] who usually have a separate Chinese name.

====Usage notes====
Many non-Christian people find this term offensive when used to refer to them. The following synonyms can be used to avoid any possible offense:

